GoodHope Asia to Start Plantation for Palm Oil in Cameroon

-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 
2011-08-09T11:54:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-09/goodhope-asia-to-start-plantation-for-palm-oil-in-cameroon.html
GoodHope  Asia  Holdings Ltd., a
Singapore based  palm-oil  processing company, plans to start a
$200 million project in Cameroon, including a 50-hectare (124-
acre) plantation, it said in a statement.  GoodHope Asia, a  unit  of Colombo-based Carson Cumberbatch
Plc, will begin operations in four years that will include a
factory to process palm oil for domestic use and for export,
Rizan Jiffrey, director of planning and business development,
said in a statement handed to reporters in Yaounde, the capital,
today. He didnâ€™t say when the project would begin.  To contact the reporter on this story:
